      "text": "STEP 1 — Distances when slow & fast MEET:\n\n  • slow traveled:  m + k\n  • fast traveled:  m + k + n·L    (fast went around the cycle n times)\n\nSTEP 2 — Fast moves at 2× speed of slow:\n\n  2 × (m + k) = m + k + n·L\n      m + k   = n·L\n          m   = n·L - k\n\nSTEP 3 — What does  m = n·L - k  mean?\n\n  Rewrite:  m = (n-1)·L + (L - k)\n\n  → A pointer starting at MEETING POINT and walking m steps\n    will complete (n-1) full cycles, then walk (L-k) more steps,\n    which lands it EXACTLY at the CYCLE START!\n\n  → A pointer starting at HEAD and walking m steps\n    also lands at the CYCLE START (by definition of m).",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "index": "aj",
      "frameId": null,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "STEP 1 — Distances when slow & fast MEET:\n\n  • slow traveled:  m + k\n  • fast traveled:  m + k + n·L    (fast went around the cycle n times)\n\nSTEP 2 — Fast moves at 2× speed of slow:\n\n  2 × (m + k) = m + k + n·L\n      m + k   = n·L\n          m   = n·L - k\n\nSTEP 3 — What does  m = n·L - k  mean?\n\n  Rewrite:  m = (n-1)·L + (L - k)\n\n  → A pointer starting at MEETING POINT and walking m steps\n    will complete (n-1) full cycles, then walk (L-k) more steps,\n    which lands it EXACTLY at the CYCLE START!\n\n  → A pointer starting at HEAD and walking m steps\n    also lands at the CYCLE START (by definition of m).",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 0.9672619047619048
    },
    {
      "id": "p2_algo_title",
