      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "index": "al",
      "frameId": null
    },
    {
      "id": "p2_algo_text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 1735,
      "width": 710,
      "height": 185,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 8003,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1487339037,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1784045621677,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. slow = head              ← Reset slow back to head\n   fast stays at meeting point\n\n2. Move BOTH by 1 step at a time:\n     slow = slow->next\n     fast = fast->next\n\n3. When slow == fast  →  That node is the CYCLE START!  ✅\n\nWhy? Because both walk exactly m steps to reach cycle start.\n        (slow walks m from head, fast walks m = (n-1)L + (L-k) inside cycle)  ∎",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "index": "am",
      "frameId": null,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. slow = head              ← Reset slow back to head\n   fast stays at meeting point\n\n2. Move BOTH by 1 step at a time:\n     slow = slow->next\n     fast = fast->next\n\n3. When slow == fast  →  That node is the CYCLE START!  ✅\n\nWhy? Because both walk exactly m steps to reach cycle start.\n        (slow walks m from head, fast walks m = (n-1)L + (L-k) inside cycle)  ∎",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.0511363636363635
    },
