    {
      "id": "ex_trace_box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 2170,
      "width": 750,
      "height": 340,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#e7f5ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 40,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 9030,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1072536371,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1784045621677,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "index": "b03",
      "frameId": null
    },
    {
      "id": "ex_trace_text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 2185,
      "width": 710,
      "height": 315,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 9031,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 867378557,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1784045621677,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Example: 1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → (back to 2)     m=1, k=2, L=3\n\nPHASE 1 — Detect cycle (slow +1, fast +2):\n  Start:    slow=1, fast=1\n  Step 1:   slow=2, fast=3\n  Step 2:   slow=3, fast=2   (fast went 3→4→2)\n  Step 3:   slow=4, fast=4   ← slow == fast! Cycle detected at node 4.\n\nPHASE 2 — Find cycle start (reset slow to head, both +1):\n  Reset:    slow=1 (head), fast=4 (meeting point)\n  Step 1:   slow=2, fast=2   (fast went 4→2)\n\n  slow == fast at node 2  →  ✅ CYCLE START FOUND!\n\nVerify: m = 1 step from head to cycle start.\n        Both pointers took exactly 1 step to meet at node 2.  ∎",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "index": "b04",
      "frameId": null,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Example: 1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → (back to 2)     m=1, k=2, L=3\n\nPHASE 1 — Detect cycle (slow +1, fast +2):\n  Start:    slow=1, fast=1\n  Step 1:   slow=2, fast=3\n  Step 2:   slow=3, fast=2   (fast went 3→4→2)\n  Step 3:   slow=4, fast=4   ← slow == fast! Cycle detected at node 4.\n\nPHASE 2 — Find cycle start (reset slow to head, both +1):\n  Reset:    slow=1 (head), fast=4 (meeting point)\n  Step 1:   slow=2, fast=2   (fast went 4→2)\n\n  slow == fast at node 2  →  ✅ CYCLE START FOUND!\n\nVerify: m = 1 step from head to cycle start.\n        Both pointers took exactly 1 step to meet at node 2.  ∎",
